<paragraph pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
Namibia (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Seydel</emphasis>
3695, 4170, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Merxmuller</emphasis>
1032, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Pearson</emphasis>
9562, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Dinter</emphasis>
4284). 1500-2000 m. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Acacia</emphasis>
bushland on sand; apparently rare.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="73" pageNumber="74" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Very distinct because of the subsessile flowers and accrescent calyx, which almost conceals the corolla.</paragraph>
